<br>
I think Bjond's point was that the tier system wasn't quite accurate.  It's a matter of how you define your requirements for being on a &quot;tier&quot;.<br>
<br>
Bjond is saying that you have to kill every mob prior to tier X in order to advance to tier X, then kill all mobs on tier X to advance to X+1.<br>
<br>
As you pointed out, that's a tad silly, because there's no real good point to kill Sontalak as long as First Brood Dragons aren't highly contested, so it's sensible for a guild to never kill Sontalak even if they've downed tier 5-6+ mobs.  <br>
<br>
Also, I'd argue that it would be possible to hypothesize a force that could kill Arch Lich, Creator, AoW, Tunare, etc that would wipe to Sont (given some bad luck).<br>
<br>
All that just means that you should take the &quot;tier&quot; system with a grain of salt.  It also means that if you're going to get into a discussion that &quot;Guild Z is or is not on Tier X&quot; you need to have the requirements for being on a given tier well defined and accepted up front.<br>
<br>
&quot;And strats on sont were not the only things people were looking for on other boards.. Someone posted they wanted the strat on 4th warder as they were the top guild. &quot;<br>
<br>
I think Fuvi asked what people thought would be a better tank for warder 4, Shadow Knight or Warrior, given that you have the minimum force to defeat warder 4 (i.e. the question is trivial if you have a considerably high amount of DPS).  Or maybe it was posed which choice of tank would allow you to kill him with less, or something like that - I don't precisely know.  From what I understand the discussion wasn't entirely enlightening (imagine that), and the post was cleared.<br>
<br>
Was there something else, does &quot;top guild&quot; there refer to Resolution?<br>
<br>
Witherweaver<br>
60 Wizard<br>
