<br>
There are some special rules for tier-7 and tier-8, though.  You have to be tier-6 and then you have to reserve a live trial for tier-7.  The 7&amp;8 trials are done with the live critters.<br>
<br>
The only issue that's kinda wrong with claiming to be on a particular tier when you haven't met the conditions for it is that it's a bit like bragging about something you have not done.  It's not that big a deal to be able to claim to have slain Tunare -- it's a step, but it's not the major thing slaying AoW is.  That's a huge one.  If you can slay AoW, imho, you're set for anything at all in EQ except for perhaps the Vulak ring.<br>
<br>
Anyway, Reso, FnF, et al, have all done some great things both for themselves and for the server, especially considering how young the server is.  FV has a really nice guild comunity.  Neither seem to me to be the type of guild that would want to claim false honors. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vampiricmuse>Vampiric Muse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/02 3:32:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1610.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eqsighost.netfirms.com/DavidStrange/vamp.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yes, you can skip tiers</span><hr size=1> am I the only one who thinks Tiers are stupid?<br>
